<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="22Nov1929"><font color="red">22 November 1929</font> <i>Letters I</i> (to Harriet Weaver, typed): James Stephens was over here for a week. I saw him nearly every day and explained to him all about the book, at least a great deal, and he promised me that if I found it was madness to continue, in my condition, and saw no other way out, that he would devote himself heart and soul to the completion of it, that is the second part and the epilogue or fourth &hellip;  I hope you like <i>Transition</i> and the use I have made of your book on the City churches </div>
